The paper focuses on the dynamics of information spread on social networks, which falls under the category of social computing (cs.SI) and social network analysis (cs.SOC). The study also involves analyzing large datasets, which could be categorized under information retrieval (cs.IR) and cyber security (cs.CYBER). Additionally, the paper discusses the structure of networks and global patterns of information flow, which could be classified under systems and control (cs.SD).
